# Line-ending policy. Without this file, Windows git (core.autocrlf=true) and
# WSL/Linux git (unset) disagree about the same working tree — one reports 2
# modified files, the other 30 with ~11k phantom line changes. That makes any
# diff-derived identity depend on the checkout environment rather than on what
# actually changed, which matters here because the benchmark's experiment_id
# includes the diff hash (benchmarks/onboard_suite/CRITERIA.md).
* text=auto eol=lf

# ── Never normalise fuzzing artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────
# These are byte-exact program inputs. `text=auto` misclassifies many of them
# as text — verified: a plain `* text=auto eol=lf` restaged 309 AFL corpus
# files, rewriting bytes inside them. A reproducer that has had CRLF collapsed
# to LF no longer reproduces, and the corruption is silent.
*.bin           -text
*.compressed    -text
*.raw           -text
*.poc           -text

# AFL++ working directories: queue entries, crash and hang reproducers,
# minimised corpora. Outputs, not sources.
**/corpus/**    -text
**/queue/**     -text
**/crashes/**   -text
**/hangs/**     -text
seeds/**        -text

